      "writtenOn": "2016-04-18T17:54:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/i18n-source-translation.html\n\u003eWhen Qt\u0027s translation tool, lupdate, is used to process a set of source files, the text wrapped in tr() calls is stored in a section of the translation file that corresponds to its translation context.\n\nThis means it would capture separate strings in tr() as a completely unrelated things, and the translator later would need to find out that the strings are somehow connected.\nUsing string formatting and having it as a single tr()-ed string fixes it\nAlso, lupdate tool can only capture string literals in the tr() call, so it anything\u0027s not a literal, it won\u0027t appear in the translation file at all",
      "parentUuid": "4881acc7_6a869f0f",
      "range": {
